---

## Requirements Checklist

| Requirement | Status | Notes |
|-------------|--------|-------|
| Keyless signing (Fulcio + Rekor) | ✅ | `COSIGN_EXPERIMENTAL=1` + OIDC |
| SBOM in SPDX format | ✅ | `syft -o spdx-json` default |
| Verify before deploy | ✅ | `verify-deployment-ready` job + scripts |
| No private keys in CI | ✅ | Keyless signing only, no keys stored |
| SLSA provenance | ✅ | `slsa-github-generator` |
| GitHub attestation | ✅ | `actions/attest-build-provenance` |
| Multi-platform builds | ✅ | `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` |
| Release artifact SBOM | ✅ | Auto-upload on tag push |

---

## Usage

```bash
# Manual signing
./scripts/sign-image.sh ghcr.io/user/ssh-manager:latest

# Verification (before deploy!)
./scripts/verify-image.sh ghcr.io/user/ssh-manager:v1.0.0

# SBOM generation
./scripts/generate-sbom.sh ghcr.io/user/ssh-manager:latest
```

---

## Security Notes

- All signing is keyless via OIDC (no private keys in CI)
- Signatures are recorded in Rekor transparency log
- Every deployment must verify image signature
- SBOMs are signed and uploaded as release artifacts
- SLSA provenance provides build traceability
